<div id="banner">
	<h1>Stanford: Eat the Whales</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>In the middle of campus a huge orange fishing net has been erected. &#8216;This net behind me is used to catch marine animals,&#8217; shouts an angry young man into a microphone. &#8216;It ends up destroying entire animal habitats. Help us stop this deadly practice and get some free fresh crab by signing our petition.&#8217; I spin around and sure enough there is a large booth that reads &#8220;FREE FRESH CRAB&#8221;. That&#8217;s one bizarre way to save nature.</p>

<p class="posted">posted April 23, 2005 03:15 PM (<a class="category" href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/cat_education">Education</a>) (<a href="001687#comments">0 comments</a>) <a href="001687" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

